# [TCPM](../wg/tcpm.html)

## Summary
The TCPM working group met at IETF 125 to discuss progress on active working group documents and several new individual proposals. Key highlights include the publication of RFC 9637, the nearing completion of the TCP ACK Rate Request (TARR) option, and discussions on enhancing TCP resets with diagnostic payloads. The group also deliberated on extending TCP Authentication Option (TCP-AO) to support Post-Quantum Cryptography (PQC) and a proposal for a TCP Provenance Identifier.

## Key Discussion Points

### Working Group Status Update
Presented by Yoshifumi Nishida.
[Slide Deck: chair slide](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-tcpm-chair-slide-00)

*   **RFC Published:** RFC 9637 (formerly draft-ietf-tcpm-6937bis) has been published.
*   **Accurate ECN:** `draft-ietf-tcpm-accurate-ecn` is currently in AUTH48.
*   **TCP Extended Data Offset (EDO):** `draft-ietf-tcpm-edo` remains a long-term item due to the complexity of extending the TCP option space.
*   **Ghost ACKs:** The chairs are waiting for a new version of `draft-ietf-tcpm-tcp-ghost-acks` from the authors before considering a Working Group Last Call (WGLC).

