### TCP RST Diagnostic Payload
Presented by Haiming Gui (Jason).
[Slide Deck: IETF 125 draft-boucadair-tcpm-rst-diagnostic-payload](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-tcpm-ietf-125-draft-boucadair-tcpm-rst-diagnostic-payload-00)
Draft: `draft-boucadair-tcpm-rst-diagnostic-payload`

*   **Overview:** This draft adds a diagnostic payload to TCP Reset (RST) packets to help operators understand why a connection was terminated.
*   **Updates:** The format was simplified from CBOR to a compact plain-text/binary format. The intended status was changed from Standards Track to Experimental.
*   **Discussion:** 
    *   Jeff Haas and Lars Eggert expressed significant security concerns regarding the "freeform description" format (UTF-8), citing risks associated with parsing complex character sets in the network stack.
    *   Michael Tuexen indicated he had only implemented the compact form in FreeBSD and did not intend to support the freeform version.
    *   There was a strong sense among those present to remove the freeform description and stick to the compact "reason code" format.

