### TCP Provenance Identifier Option
Presented by the author.
[Slide Deck: TCP Provenance Identifier Option](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-tcpm-tcp-provenance-identifier-option-00)

*   **Overview:** Proposes a TCP option to carry a provenance identifier (Host IP + Process ID) to track the origin of connections across middleboxes (NATs, L7 proxies) in managed environments like data centers.
*   **Discussion:** 
    *   Lars Eggert and Magnus Westerlund questioned the need for an IETF standard for a solution intended for controlled, single-operator data centers where middleboxes could be configured without a new TCP option.
    *   Zhong Lenli raised privacy concerns regarding the leakage of internal Process IDs (PIDs) in plain text.
    *   Mia Killevein suggested looking at QUIC connection migration and its privacy-preserving mechanisms as a point of comparison.

